Will there be a year-end rally on the stock market? Experts share their views on the "subprime" crisis
Less than five weeks before the end of the fiscal year, investors are already rubbing their hands and can't wait for the usual end of the year.
This year, however, it is not clear to experts whether this will actually happen.
According to Banif, “from a statistical point of view, the stock market generally behaves positively in December.
However, forecasts with a purely statistical background are not necessarily correct, in fact, the market is characterised by uncertainty in the current situation, at least in the short term".
Experts are far from advocating the stock market's year-end swing, although they state that "the stock market is maintained by the presence of liquidity, this gives an opportunity to invest because there are no guaranteed alternatives, especially fixed returns, which are negatively affected by the escape to quality securities, both in the long and in the short term".
As a result, they believe that the stock market will be characterised by a lateral movement that is not free of volatility, "especially since the impact of the Fed rate reduction is unknown at the moment, as the price of crude oil is high and inflationary tension is also threatened".
Javier Barrio, BPI’s sales manager in Spain, agrees, so it would be risky to say that there will be a rally.
According to the expert, "the situation is not at all rosy."
Ibex lost nearly 4 percent of the highest figures recorded on November 8, when the index closed at 15,945.7 points.
However, not all experts are so obnoxious.
According to Intermoney analyst Juan Solana, Ibex 35 could close the year closer to 16,000 points due to the restructuring of wallets and payments to the usual pension fund.
On the other hand, the expert adds that some changes are expected this year, as the rally shifts to the second week of December, the week after the long weekend of the celebration of the Constitution.
The analyst considers it unlikely that volatility will affect market trends.
Federico Olucha, an analyst at Inversis Banco, said: "We are close to the technical level and are experiencing a decline in the stock market index, which may increase depending on the news from the United States, in terms of the consequences of the credit market crisis."
Analysts are confident that these will be beneficial.
Analysts agree on which securities will be aimed at achieving Ibex's new maximum quotas.
Solana, from Intermoney, emphasizes that "this year it's the big securities."
The expert would add the two big banks and some construction companies to the list, “because by then the electric sector will be very expensive.”
Federico Olucha from Inversis Banco states that the increase is due to the banking sector and the industrial sector.
The rally can also be positive for construction companies, if at all.
"ACS has been trying to regain its position for several months and we hope that Ferrovial and FCC construction companies will follow suit," he said.
Cyclical consumption will be the main player for the rest of the year due to the increase in sales during the Christmas sales period.
On the other hand, according to the expert, technology companies can also benefit, although there is not too much representation in the Spanish market in this area.
Five times in seven years
In the last seven years, there have been only two falls in the December exchange rate.
The real year-end rally was observed in 2003 when stock markets emerged from the crisis caused by the bursting of the technological bubble.
This year, when Ibex 35 corrected 28.17 percent, a 6.68% jump was recorded in December.
So it is still open whether 2007 will be the fifth consecutive profitable year (currently Ibex shows an increase of 8.36% since January) and whether the end rally can take place.
Banco Popular Spanish opens an account open 12 hours from Monday to Saturday
Banco Popular Spain has decided to renovate most of its branches.
This concerns a total of 200 branches located in the most commercially affected parts of Spain.
These branches run under the name Popular Max and make a big difference to the bank.
However, it is also for other Spanish institutions, as this is the first group whose branches are unusually open continuously until 20.30 p.m. and even on Saturdays from 10 a.m. to 20.30 p.m.
The other group, BBVA, which has also repeatedly said that it plans to extend the opening of its accounts, has not yet taken the necessary steps.
But he's just about to reach an agreement with the unions to close 75% of his branches in exchange for opening one afternoon, although not to the public.
The experience of Banco Popular Spain will be crucial for the other institutions, as this will be the basis for deciding whether to join the initiative in favour of better opening of shops.
This is precisely the objective of the Banco Popular Spain project.
In these places, they would like to target shopping individuals, small and medium-sized enterprises, individual entrepreneurs and local businesses.
The bank wants to operate 200 branches across Spain for 18 months with the already mentioned opening hours, as it is not a new opening order, but a modification of the existing one.
To do this, the institution modernizes its branches in commercial zones according to the needs of the customers of each street.
In this way, the extension of the opening hours is accompanied by a new idea of the nature of the drawers, a more modern, colorful design.
Ángel Rivera, responsible for commercial banks, points out that restructuring does not require a large investment, but they have to employ more employees, which means eight or nine employees per branch instead of the current six.
Branches, which even include meeting rooms for SMEs, will also sell non-financial products.
Favorable experiences
Banco Popular has already implemented the initiative in its three Madrid branches.
According to Ángel Rivero, the experience was positive.
The drawers on the streets of Bravo Murillo, O'Donnell and Gran Vía in Madrid were chosen, and Rivero said the decision was the right one.
Banco Popular Spain currently has 2,500 accounts.
Another 60 operate under the name Mundocredit, specializes in immigrants, and also has very favorable opening hours, even on Sundays and holidays.
In these units of PopularMax, they do not use the BBVA model, where some branches offer a wide range of non-financial products.
“We don’t want to create competition for our customers,” Rivero says.
At the moment, they have reached an agreement with Telefónica and will sell mobile phones using external staff.
Telecinco doubles the stock market value of its rival Antena 3 for the first time
"We did it."
With this sentence, Paolo Vasile, acting advisor to Telecinco, expressed his satisfaction at the closing of the market yesterday when it turned out that the TV station he led doubled the value of his rival Antena 3.
Yet one thing overshadowed his joy: "It only hurts that it's not because we've risen more, but because we've fallen less," he said.
Even so, he placed great emphasis on the fact that we "falled less" in the weak market.
Telecinco closed yesterday with a 2.54% increase.
This puts its annual loss at 15.66 percent.
The company owns 52 percent of Mediaset, 13 percent of Vocento, so its stock market value, according to Bloomberg data, is EUR 4.488.88 million.
His rival, Antena 3, lost 1.52% yesterday and has fallen 40.5 percent since January, so yesterday it was worth half, 2.193.46 million.
The value of the other listed communication companies is 3.571 million for Sogecable; 2.518.53 million for Prisa (published by Cinco Días) and 1.779 million for Vocento.
According to Vasile, the comparison with Antena 3 is due to the similarity between the two companies.
The only question is how much we can deliver in the same market, at what cost, and how all this will pay off in terms of ratings.
Last week, Telecinco announced its intention to become the first TV channel with gross advertising revenue of more than $1 billion this year, said Giuseppe Tringali, acting advisor to Telecinco and Publiespa.
If the announced fact is realized, compared to the 965.4 million recorded in the 2006 financial year, the TV channel would increase its advertising revenues by 3.6 percent in this financial year.
Net sales of Antena 3 increased by 1.6 percent in the first nine months of the fiscal year (thus reaching 734.4 million), while net sales of television increased by 0.7 percent (630.4 million).
According to analysts, one of the factors that has triggered Telecinco's stock market momentum is the high pay-out that has been maintained so far: in 2006, the company led by President Alejandro Echevarría distributed 100% of its profits to its shareholders.
According to Vasile, although it is too early to decide, this ratio may change after buying 33% of Endemol in association with its parent company Mediaset.
“We officially guarantee a minimum payout of 50%, although we have always distributed a lot more.
I hope our shareholders will be happy with us this year, as we have already favored them with the acquisition of 33% of Endemol.”
According to analysts, the market is currently experiencing some slowdowns.
Lehman Brothers recently reduced its yield estimates for Telecinco by 4 percent in 2008 and 7 percent in 2009.
According to them, this is due to an estimated decrease in sales revenue from 10.5% to 8.4% in 2008 and from 5.5% to 5.1% in 2009.
According to the same company's forecasts, Antena 3's profits will fall by 4.5 percent in 2008 and 7.5 percent in 2009.
3 reviews
1.
Ibersecurity: proposes the purchase of both securities, mainly due to the high profitability and long-term sustainable potential of dividends.
2.
Caja Madrid: sees Telecinco as more favorable (acquisition) than Antena 3 (retention) due to its "multiple attractiveness" and business strengthening.
3.
JPMorgan: In both cases, it recommends underweighting due to "similar risks" (saturated market and less favourable economic climate).
Congress approves the takeover of MiFID, which entered into force on 1 November
In parallel with the parliamentary process, which ended today with the congressional vote approving the Senate amendments, the government has initiated a social dialogue on the legislation on which the law is based, so that both can enter into force before the end of the year.
Representatives of the various groups unanimously highlighted the efforts made by Members and Senators in negotiations and agreements to establish the most favourable normative to protect investors and to regulate the activities of companies in detail in order to operate effectively in the market.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, allows for the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, broadening the supervisory rights of the Spanish National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between different supervisors of the European Union.
The new directive allows financial advisory services for specialised companies, but also for natural or legal persons, as well as for securities distribution companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies, to establish a new form of financial services company (ESIS), namely financial advisory companies (AFI).
In addition, the law increases the number of systems capable of carrying out operations involving funds, thus adding multilateral trading platforms and order-executing internalisation systems to regulated secondary markets, which compete with current stock exchange participants.
In addition, the Act requires investment service providers to provide market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk-taking and risk management methods, and to facilitate the control of CNMV, they must keep records of all operations carried out.
The Congressional Economic Commission has introduced a number of amendments. Of these, it is of paramount importance that securitised debts are treated as "complex" funds due to the high risk they pose to the investor. This has been proven in the context of high-risk mortgage lending in the United States (subprime).
On the other hand, the transposition of the directive was also used to legally outline the scope of activities of those with economic and business qualifications, 30 years after the royal decree defining the professional functions that can only be carried out by economists came into force in 1977.
And the Senate has proposed the creation of new players in the financial sector, such as the brokerage agent who works for another account, does not need the permission of CNMV and can market products or acquire customers for several investment companies at the same time.
The Consumer Price Index increased by 0.5 points in November and reached 4.1%.
This indicator, which Eurostat takes into account to calculate the inflation rate in the European Union, shows the evolution of prices in Spain for the month of November.
Its publication is in line with the strategy of Eurostat and the European Central Bank to provide data that are comparable to data from the United States, both in terms of time and nature.
The same calculation method is used for the preliminary indicator as for the calculation of the Combined Price Index, but the statistical modelling method differs to estimate information that is not yet available at the time of publication.
The Statistical Office pointed out that the preliminary indicator is purely indicative and may therefore deviate from the final data, which will be published on 14 December.
"The consumer price index remains relatively high."
Pedro Solbes, a vice-president of the government and Minister of Economic Affairs, stated that the increase in the Consumer Price Index to 4.1% in November is only "temporary", but at the same time predicted that the price index is expected to be "relatively high" in the coming months.
In Parliament's corridors, Solbes confirmed that "although the indicator is not very favourable", the inflation rate in Spain has remained more or less at the same level within the monetary union in recent years.
He added that the month of November was “less surprising” than the previous month, when the Government did not expect such a large increase.
“We expected a value of around 4%,” the Minister of Economic Affairs acknowledged in connection with the data published today.
