Mayor of Totana Arrested in Suspected Corruption Case
Earlier this morning, the Gendarmerie arrested the mayor of Totana, a town in Murcia province, on suspicion of being involved in an urban corruption scandal this week.
Besides him, they arrested one of the city hall's secretaries and the town's chief of police.
Former city council member José Martínez Andreo took over the place of the EPP representative Juan Morales in May, who, according to the official bodies interviewed by the SER radio channel, could have been the head of the corruption network.
Police continue to investigate the city's offices and the City Development Council, and further arrests cannot be excluded.
Juan Morales’ lawyer was also investigated as the main suspect in the corruption scandal that broke out this week.
According to the SER radio station, the lawyer of the People's Party Juan Morales was arrested when he left Morales with documents related to corruption in his bag.
According to police sources, the subject of the investigation is the alleged commission that Morales received in exchange for signing an urban development agreement with a Galician construction company on the reclassification of 200 hectares of land.
Eight people are currently under arrest.
Bono accepts the nomination of the PSOE in Toledo and the President of Parliament if they win the elections.
The former Minister of Defence, José Bono, accepted the offer of the Prime Minister and the Secretary-General of the Socialist Party, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero, to lead the PSOE list in the next parliamentary elections in Toledo and to chair Parliament if the Socialists win the elections.
