What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which provides security to the owner of the car against various damage events, is significant and depends on several factors, such as age, gender, date of acquisition of the driving licence, marital status, type and use of the car to be insured.
Buying a car is just the first step.
In fact, choosing the right insurance is often more difficult than deciding what kind of car you want.
First of all, we need to be clear about what this is about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement takes the form of an insurance contract, which states that the insurance company undertakes to pay compensation for the fixed insurance premium in the event of the occurrence of the damage.
The insurance premium is practically the amount paid for the insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining a driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured, its use, and so on.
Insurance companies set the insurance premium on the basis of statistics, i.e. a higher amount is paid by the person who represents a higher risk of accident.
That’s why people over the age of 25 or women pay less because, according to statistics, they pose a lower risk because they are more careful.
Similarly, according to the statements, insurance companies concluded that married people cause fewer accidents than lonely people.
For the type of use of the car, the frequency is decisive.
With more frequent use, the possibility of an accident increases.
Insurance companies take a number of factors into account when setting insurance premiums.
Therefore, the owner should carefully look into it so that he can choose the most suitable form of insurance for his profile.
The following are the most important factors in choosing to best adapt to the needs of the insured person and to establish an acceptable price.
When concluding an insurance contract, people under the age of 25 face a number of disadvantages, such as lack of driving experience and freshness of driving license.
Although it is ideal to be insured against all dangers, there are also more economical solutions.
More cautious drivers can take out a complete insurance with a self-part, thus ensuring against all dangers and the price will be affordable.
For this type of contract, the insured pays part of the damage.
“The amount of the deductible to be paid by the insured depends on the insurance premium; the higher the premium, the lower the deductible,” says Luis Noguera, First Europe’s Spanish head of internet insurance brokerage.
Another option is extended liability insurance to third parties when the customer insures himself against damage to others, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it will be insured against theft, fire damage and the loss of the car.
A word of advice.
If you are not yet 25 years old, be careful and avoid accidents if possible, as this will affect the bonus and thus reduce the amount to be paid in the future.
It is called a bonus in relation to the basic tariff of the insurance company.
And the penalty imposed compared to the basic tariff is called malus.
"The amount of bonus and rasp depends on the insurance company and its profits.
If the company had a good year, it can afford to raise the bonus rate,” Noguera explains.
Once the age limit of 25 has been exceeded, it is easier for owners to take out adequate insurance, as the risk of accidents is reduced due to the experience gained over the years.
At this point, we advise you to take out a full insurance.
"In general, young people are not yet able to apply their experience properly in an accident or even when driving," says the director of the European insurance company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of driving, when drivers have already overcome the fear of beginners.
If the insured person is already married but does not have children yet, it is best to take out a complete insurance policy, of course, if your financial possibilities allow it.
Insurance companies consider married couples with children to be the least risky customers, so in their case the fee to be paid is also lower.
In this case, it is best to have a full insurance deductible (up to 300 euros), or if you have a higher bonus, you can extend the insurance to damage caused to others from the third year of the vehicle.
"They drive more calmly, but at the same time have more purchasing power and can afford to have a higher share," Luis Noguera confirms.
In the case of pensioners, we recommend the full insurance with a self-part (which is around 150 euros) or in the case of a higher bonus, it can be extended to liability insurance.
Car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it protects the owner in the event of damage, but also because it is a large expense, so it is essential to choose the right form of insurance.
