The two companies jointly founded the MSP joint venture to take over the competing Freenet.
The two companies will initially be satisfied with a good ten percent stake in Freenet and will not exercise their right to take over another 18.49 percent of Freenet, United Internet said on Thursday.
However, the two companies will leave all options open, especially with regard to the increase in the shareholding in Freenet AG.
Negotiations between the United Internet and Freenet on the strategic partnership were completed in mid-November.
The poker game around Freenet has been going on for months and is now part of the consolidation of the German telecommunications market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million contract mobile phone customers and 1.27 million DSL and fixed access customers.
The holding company, formed by United Internet and Drillisch, had a direct stake of 6.01 percent in Freenet.
It has now been agreed that Drillisch will bring in an additional 4%.
The acquisition of 18.49 percent of the Vatas investment company was agreed in August.
